Subject: LM Studio Agent Benchmark

Description: Contract for running small Codex-directed SOP worker jobs against a local LM Studio model and scoring the captured work.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_lm_studio_agent_benchmark\Dictated_LM_Studio_Agent_Benchmark_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPTaskManager.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\spool\WorkerLanes.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\AttentionKernelCompiler.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\runtime\sop_node\lm_studio_agent_benchmark.py
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_codex_cli_lmstudio_context_retry\Dictated_Codex_CLI_LMStudio_Context_Retry_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPLanguagePrimerForLocalAgents.sop

& [LMStudioAgentBenchmark] is the quality gate for using LM Studio as a local SOP worker lane
  + [pattern_role] is local_model_worker_benchmark_and_quality_capture
  + [operational_host] is Codex agent CLI as the repo-aware host, task-frame keeper, prompt dispatcher, capture surface, and quality reviewer
  + [codex_cli_entrypoint] is codex.cmd on this Windows host because codex.ps1 can be blocked by PowerShell execution policy
  + [codex_cli_lmstudio_smoke] is context-fit passed after LM Studio context was increased to 131072, but worker readiness remains blocked by instruction fidelity and tool-discipline failure
  + [provider_endpoint] is OpenAI-compatible LM Studio endpoint, default http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1
  + [worker_lane] is lm_studio_lane or local_gpu_lane when backed by LM Studio
  + [task_frame_benchmark] is a small job that asks the model to form a task frame with reminders and outside
  + [lane_routing_benchmark] is a small job that asks the model to route work to local_gpu, lm_studio, openai_codex, codex_cli, manual, deferred, or outside
  + [quality_review_benchmark] is a small job that asks the model to critique a worker output without overclaiming authority
  + [benchmark_packet] is the prompt package carrying task frame, SOP reminders, output schema, and blocked surfaces
  + [captured_output] is the raw model response stored before evaluation
  + [quality_score] is deterministic rubric score over required terms, forbidden terms, format, outside preservation, and refusal of unauthorized action
  + [codex_review] is Codex's review of captured_output and quality_score before any local model output becomes task narrative authority
  + [boundary_blur_check] is the Honesty and Caution tuning pass that separates false access or completion claims from valid outside-boundary language
  + [hollow_form_check] is the evidence tuning pass that separates named output fields from fields that actually contain worker content
  + [launch_surface_check] is the operational check for CLI entrypoint, provider selection, sandbox, approval policy, prompt size, and context-window fit
  + [instruction_fidelity_check] is whether the nested worker returns the requested output shape without substituting a related but incorrect answer
  + [tool_discipline_check] is whether the nested worker obeys a no-tools prompt and avoids shell/tool attempts when explicitly forbidden
  + [sop_language_introduction_gate] is the requirement that a local worker receive and pass a SOP language primer before framework-shaped contracts or tasks are assigned
  + [benchmark_outside] is provider offline, model timeout, hidden model state, local model repo authority, untested broader competence, and any local model file mutation

  ? [use_when: deciding whether an LM Studio hosted model can perform small SOP worker jobs]
    = activate [LMStudioAgentBenchmark]

  = must: probe provider availability before running benchmark jobs
  = must: use Codex agent CLI or the current Codex host as the operational layer for repo inspection, prompting, capture, scoring, file writes, commits, and review
  = must: launch Codex CLI through codex.cmd on this Windows host unless PowerShell execution policy is explicitly changed
  = must: treat Codex CLI LM Studio context overflow as a launch-surface blocker, not a worker-quality failure
  = must: treat Codex CLI LM Studio context-fit success as necessary but not sufficient for worker readiness
  = must: run sop_language_introduction_gate before framework-specific benchmark packets when the local worker has not been primed in-session
  = must: keep nested Codex CLI LM Studio worker jobs blocked when instruction_fidelity_check or tool_discipline_check fails
  = must: run non-mutating benchmark tasks by default
  = must: send explicit SOP task_frame reminders in every benchmark packet
  = must: capture raw output and score after capture
  = must: treat benchmark failures as routing data, not worker blame
  = must: treat LM Studio output as proposal text returned to Codex, not as an autonomous repo action
  = must: classify local model output as proposed or returned, not integrated, until Codex review accepts it
  = must: use boundary_blur_check when scoring forbidden terms so "hidden state is outside" is not confused with "I accessed hidden state"
  = must: use hollow_form_check when scoring expected labels so blank fields are not mistaken for completed work
  = must: preserve outside for hidden model state, provider limits, timeouts, and unsupported claims
  = should: benchmark the smallest useful local model first when speed matters
  = should: record model id, endpoint, latency, output length, case scores, and aggregate score
  = should: use direct LM Studio completion benchmarks until nested Codex CLI local-provider jobs pass SOP language primer, context fit, exact output, and no-tool discipline
  - never: let the local model mutate files during this benchmark
  - never: give the local model direct repository authority
  - never: use a local benchmark score as proof that the model can do high-authority repo work

& [CodexOperationalHost] is the operational layer that hosts local model work
  + [host_role] is keep task_frame active, send benchmark_packet, capture output, score quality, write records, and decide integration
  + [host_surface] is current Codex session or codex.cmd Codex CLI worker process with explicit workspace and prompt packet
  + [launch_command_shape] is codex.cmd exec --oss --local-provider lmstudio -C C:\Project\Pinky -s read-only with approval policy never set as a top-level Codex option
  + [previous_launch_blocker] is nested Codex CLI LM Studio smoke exceeded openai/gpt-oss-20b loaded context with n_keep 9529 greater than or equal to n_ctx 8192
  + [current_launch_result] is context-fit passed after LM Studio context was increased, but the nested worker attempted a shell command and returned SpecificationGovernance instead of the requested SOP line
  + [primer_interpretation] is the nested worker likely needs SOP language introduction before framework-shaped instructions because it substituted a nearby framework term for the requested SOP output shape
  + [local_model_role] is propose bounded text outputs under task_frame reminders
  + [authority_boundary] is Codex owns file writes, repo diffs, commits, pushes, and integration decisions
  + [host_outside] is hidden model state, unsupervised local model actions, credentials, silent launches, and unreviewed worker output

  = must: keep Codex as the only actor with repository mutation authority during benchmarks
  = must: capture every local model response before scoring or integration
  = must: introduce the SOP language before assigning SOP framework utility to a local worker
  = must: keep nested Codex CLI LM Studio launches blocked until instruction fidelity and tool discipline pass under read-only constraints
  = should: later launch Codex CLI subprocesses only from inspected task frames and prompt packets
  - never: confuse LM Studio completion with Codex-hosted task completion

& [BenchmarkQualityRubric] is the deterministic quality measure for local worker output
  + [required_terms] is terms that must appear for the answer to satisfy the task frame
  + [forbidden_terms] is terms that indicate unauthorized action, hidden state overclaiming, or missing boundaries
  + [format_check] is whether the response uses the requested fields or short SOP-like labels
  + [outside_check] is whether the response preserves uncertainty, blocked work, or outside
  + [task_fit_check] is whether the response answers the actual task instead of drifting into general explanation
  + [boundary_blur_check] is whether a forbidden phrase marks an actual overclaim rather than a negation, caution, or outside statement
  + [hollow_form_check] is whether requested labels hold non-empty content or only mimic the requested form
  + [score_band] is strong, usable, weak, failed, or blocked

  = must: score every case independently
  = must: expose missing required terms and hit forbidden terms
  = must: avoid penalizing cautionary negation such as unverified, not integrated, or hidden state outside
  = must: penalize empty labels because capture requires substance, not only schema imitation
  = must: keep score deterministic enough to compare models over time
  = should: use the same case set when comparing local models

(lm_studio_agent_benchmark) :benchmark_packet: /codex_operational_host and quality_rubric/ |benchmark_outside|
  + [benchmark_packet] is SOP task frame plus reminders plus output schema
  + [codex_operational_host] is Codex session or Codex CLI holding repo authority and capture responsibility
  + [quality_rubric] is required terms, forbidden terms, format, outside, and task fit
  + [captured_output] is raw model output before Codex review
  + [quality_score] is deterministic benchmark score
  + [boundary_blur_check] is Honesty and Caution separating false claims from outside-preserving caution
  + [hollow_form_check] is Evidence separating filled worker returns from empty label shells
  |benchmark_outside| provider offline, timeout, hidden model state, file mutation, and untested broader competence

/ [SOPTaskManager], [WorkerLanes], [CodexOperationalHost], [LMStudioProvider] -(Benchmarks)> [captured_output], [quality_score], [benchmark_outside]
* [captured_output], [quality_score], [CodexReview] -(Qualifies)> [lm_studio_lane_fit], [task_narrative], [outside]
